name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Just as we have acted decisively to protect the health of Australians, based on the best evidence and medical advice, our support package responds to the economic challenges presented by this pandemic in a timely, proportionate and targeted way.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Our package also includes $1 billion to support those sectors, regions and communities that have been greatly affected by the economic impacts of #coronavirus, including those heavily reliant on industries such as tourism, agriculture and education.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: And we’re providing a cash flow boost of up to $25,000 for small and medium businesses that have staff, to protect jobs and help them build back stronger. The payment will be tax free ➡  http://aus.pm/y9za

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: We’re also increasing the instant asset write off threshold from $30,000 to $150,000 and expanding access to include businesses with annual turnover of less than $500 million (up from $50 million) until 30 June 2020.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: It includes a $750 one-off payment to pensioners, low-income families, veterans & other income support recipients & eligible concession card holders. Payments will start from 31 Mar 2020 on a progressive basis, with most expected to be made by mid-April ➡  http://aus.pm/ckp2

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: I’d like to thank them for their patience and understanding as we work to keep Australians safe during this outbreak. Thank you also to all the others involved in the operation. The next group of Australians on Christmas Island are due to head home later this week.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Some positive news with the first group of over 200 Australian citizens and permanent residents we helped get out of Wuhan leaving Christmas Island today to head home after completing the quarantine period recommended by our health experts, without anyone developing Coronavirus. pic.twitter.com/bGqLDAv9An

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Great to catch up with @ABCaustralia Chair @ItaButtrose this morning. Joined also by Minister @PaulFletcherMP and ABC MD David Anderson. Rural and regional services were a key focus of our discussion. So pleased Ita took on this job. pic.twitter.com/VaoXSAYcYX

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Our focus remains on keeping Australians safe. I’d like to thank all those people who are doing the right thing and self-isolating for up to 14 days where they think they might have been exposed to Coronavirus.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: A further 36 Australian citizens and residents who were on the Air New Zealand flight out of Wuhan have now arrived safely on Christmas Island. Thank you to all those who were involved in this operation.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Caught up with @AlanJones on @2GB873 today to discuss our ongoing response to Coronavirus to keep Australians safe and our announcement of a rolling Commission into veteran suicide and causes to help save lives. #Listen to the full interview ⬇ https://www.2gb.com/scott-morrison-confirms-australias-plans-for-mass-coronavirus-outbreak/ …

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Last month we committed an initial $50 million for wildlife aid. Dr Sally Box, who is chairing a panel of experts to advise the Government, also updated me on work to develop a longer-term plan on how we protect these beautiful creatures and restore the habitat they call home.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: One of the heart-breaking things about the devastating bushfires has been the toll they've taken on our beloved native wildlife. Today I met with the Threatened Species Commissioner & the Environment Minister to get an update on efforts to protect & treat injured wildlife. pic.twitter.com/OdisVzJcfX

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Our veterans and all serving men and women protect our community and our freedoms. It is our duty to do the same for them. https://twitter.com/TheTodayShow/status/1224795699554013186 …

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: This is about being forever vigilant for the care and well-being of our veterans. It’s our duty to protect our service men and women just as they’ve protected our community and our freedoms.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: We need to do more than a Royal Commission that looks at the past. That’s why we’re establishing a national and permanent rolling Commission into veteran suicide and its prevention with the full powers of a Royal Commission. https://twitter.com/bennyglish/status/1224651629401559040 …

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Today on #WorldCancerDay, we acknowledge all those who are in the fight of their lives and remember those who lost their battle. name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Today we gather to mourn, honour and reflect on the Black Summer that continues. We also give thanks for the selflessness, courage, sacrifice and generosity that met these fires time and again, and continue to. #Watch my full speech  https://youtu.be/FdjjeUex-ho  pic.twitter.com/7Vxb9NeWSi

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: We owe it to those we have lost, we owe it to those who have fought these fires, we owe it to our children and to the land itself to learn from the lessons that are necessary.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: I intend to advise the Governor-General to appoint former Chief of the Defence Force Mark Binskin to lead the Commission, which will shine a light on what needs to be done to make our country safer and our communities more resilient.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Today, I've written to the Premiers and Chief Minister to seek their feedback on draft terms of reference for a Royal Commission into National Natural Disaster Arrangements, following the terrible bushfires.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet:
We are now working with the Chinese authorities on a possible second assisted departure flight for Australians seeking to leave Wuhan.

We are also working with the New Zealand Government to access seats on their plane, subject to availability.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Thank you to everyone involved in what has been a complex and very challenging operation, from our medical staff, Qantas ground and air crew to Australian diplomats and other officials. I particularly want to thank the Chinese Government for their cooperative approach.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: All Australians who were on our flight out of Wuhan have arrived safely. 241 have now been transferred to Christmas Island and are being well looked after. A pregnant woman and her partner have been transferred to Perth and are in isolation there.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet:

name: Scott Morrison
tweet:
Today NSW Premier @GladysB and I signed a landmark agreement between our two governments to lower power prices, reduce emissions and get more gas into our energy supply.

On Wednesday I said we need to get the gas and today we have announced a landmark agreement to get the gas. pic.twitter.com/Q55UavOlEa

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Today Abbey & Lily joined me to lay a wreath at our National Emergency Services Memorial to thank all those giving so much in response to the terrible natural disasters that have impacted our nation. We also remember the brave firefighters who lost their lives fighting the fires. pic.twitter.com/S8zBrDfUt8

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Despite the many challenges we face, especially the terrible bushfires, the drought & the floods, today is when we can reflect upon & celebrate our great nation. Today we can all come together as one & give thanks for being Australian. Happy Australia Day! https://bit.ly/36tJtui

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Thousands of volunteer and paid responders have been working around the clock, day and night, week after week to protect property and save lives. Their courage has been extraordinary, and it’s a spirit which we must honour and celebrate this Australia Day.  http://aus.pm/og21

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: We will formally recognise and honour our brave emergency service personnel and volunteers who have given significant service to fighting these terrible bushfires with a National Emergency Medal. https://twitter.com/dailytelegraph/status/1221179810359148545 …

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: All of this year’s recipients and finalists have inspired, led and lived and shown the best of Australia's values. Thank you.

tweet:

#AusoftheYear pic.twitter.com/EJVYiddA9J

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: These terrible bushfires have taken a big toll on Australia but it’s heart-warming to see how Australians are coming together to support and help each other get through. Australia really is the best place in the world to live. https://twitter.com/AlanTudgeMP/status/1220917604417556480 …

tweet: Thank you also to President @realDonaldTrump, Vice President @Mike_Pence and @SecPompeo for your continuous and steadfast support for Australia at this difficult time 🇦🇺🇺🇸

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: It is heartening to work side-by-side with our closest friend the United States at a time of crisis and great loss. We are always friends who stand together.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Our hearts are with the loved ones, friends and colleagues who are suffering the loss of these committed firefighters, who put their lives on the line to keep our communities safe.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: On behalf of the Australian people, I express our deepest condolences on the tragic loss of 3 US firefighters in yesterday's Large Air Tanker crash that occurred while they were fighting the terrible Australian #bushfires.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Thank you Julia for your condolences. Our family greatly appreciates your kind wishes.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Deeply saddened to learn of the death of 3 people in the crash of a C130 fire fighting aircraft, north east of Cooma in NSW earlier today. My deepest condolences to the loved ones, friends and colleagues of those who have lost their lives. Such a terrible tragedy.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Good news that 28,900 new jobs were created last month, bringing the number of jobs created since we came into government to over 1.5 million. The unemployment rate is at 5.1% and the level is now lower than at the 2019, 2016 and 2013 election.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Thank you. Thank you so much to all our friends who have stepped up to help us in our time of need. https://twitter.com/DeptDefence/status/1219816846225895425 …

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: We have the best health system in the world and we are prepared to deal with this situation. While Australians should remain alert, they should not be alarmed.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Our National Incident Response Centre has been activated and is helping coordinate our response with Commonwealth medical experts working together with states and territories.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: We have put in place new measures to protect Australians with biosecurity and health officials now meeting every flight from Wuhan for screening. DFAT has raised the level of its travel advisory for Wuhan City, recommending travellers exercise a high degree of caution there.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Update on coronavirus situation. I’m advised by the Chief Medical Officer the risk of transmission in Australia remains low, however the situation is evolving.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Prof Murphy, with his state medical colleagues, has initiated measures to mitigate infectious persons entering Australia. We are well prepared to respond to this situation and we will continue to monitor and take action where necessary.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: We will be raising the level of our travel advice for Wuhan City to level 2 - exercise a high degree of caution. I urge all Australians travelling to check the DFAT Smartraveller website for specific updates.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: This afternoon I was briefed by the Chief Medical Officer Prof Brendan Murphy on the coronavirus detected in China’s Wuhan area. The CMO has advised that while the current risk level is low, precautions are being taken to protect Australians.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Peter has played a key role in Tasmania’s turnaround under Will Hodgman. We worked closely together as Treasurers and I look forward to working with him again around the COAG table.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Congratulations to Peter Gutwein on being sworn in today as Tasmania’s new Premier, taking over from @WillHodgman. I have spoken to Peter today to wish him all the best.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Small businesses in bushfire affected areas are doing it tough. Today we announced grants of $50,000 and a suite of other immediate measures to support them. Whatever it takes and whatever it costs, we’re going to help these regions to recover and rebuild.  http://aus.pm/tl4u

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: We’ve heard from local tourism operators, industry leaders, communities & the states & territories around the country. Their message is to act now & that's what we're doing. We’ll work closely with them all to deliver on our recovery plan to get these regions back up & running.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Australian tourism is facing its biggest challenge in living memory, and not just in the bushfire affected areas. One in 13 Australian jobs rely on tourism and hospitality. Read more ➡  http://aus.pm/3wxp

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Tourism businesses, employees and fire-affected communities around the country will receive much needed support from the Government’s National Bushfire Recovery Fund, through our $76m tourism recovery package. This will help protect jobs, small businesses and local economies. pic.twitter.com/ZortrVnoJ7

name: Scott Morrison
tweet:
94 New Zealand, 49 Singapore, 100 Papua New Guinea Defence Force and 70 Japanese personnel are also directly supporting operations. We thank all of them for their service. 

#OpBushfireAssist
#YourADF

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: A quick update on the deployment of our defence forces on Operation Bushfire Assist. 3,449 permanent ADF and 2,966 reservists are now directly supporting operations in NSW, Victoria, SA and Tasmania. pic.twitter.com/QP4oFxC2ja

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Once again our mobile teams are out in #bushfire areas in small towns today with social workers. And all recovery centres are staffed. We have a long way to go to recover from these terrible fires. We will be out there every day supporting these communities to do just that.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: A quick update. 46,877 claims for Federal Gov Disaster Recovery Payments have been paid, totalling $55.8m in assistance. This includes payments for 23,101 children. From Monday, an additional $400 will be paid to families for these children as many prepare to go back to school.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: In times like this, when we’re seeing such devastation from these terrible bushfires, people turn to our amazing charities for help along with their governments. Today we met in Canberra with those charities to align what we’re doing & ensure help is getting where it’s needed. pic.twitter.com/ewlYmhKn1P

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: An additional $10 million will also be invested in financial counselling services in affected areas, including extra support for the National Debt Helpline. The NDH can be accessed on 1800 007 007 or by visiting  http://www.ndh.org.au

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Emergency relief funding will be increased by $40m for affected communities. These extra funds can be used for food vouchers or to pay for a broad range of basics like clothing and petrol. It will be administered through the Salvation Army and St Vincent De Paul Society.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: We’re doubling bushfire disaster recovery payments for children, as part of the $58m package announced today to support  families and communities affected by the ongoing bushfire disaster  http://aus.pm/80hu

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Will Hodgman is a Tasmanian and Liberal legend. He has led an extraordinary turnaround in Tasmania and has set his state up for the future. As Australia’s senior Premier, he will be greatly missed around the COAG table where he made a tremendous contribution. pic.twitter.com/yE3HI1NbPT

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: We will continue to do whatever is needed to support those Australians affected and traumatised by these bushfires by rebuilding communities and helping people in need to recover ➡️  https://www.pm.gov.au/media/immediate-mental-health-services-deployed-fire-affected-communities …

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: This money will fund free counselling sessions, extra Medicare and tele-health consultations, an expansion of headspace services for young Australians, and community recovery initiatives.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: These terrible bushfires have taken a traumatic emotional toll on our people. That’s why today we’re putting an initial $76 million into immediately providing more mental health support services to firefighters, emergency personnel, and others impacted by the ongoing disaster.

name: Scott Morrison
tweet: Tomorrow I’ll be appearing live on @abcnews for an in-depth discussion with @David_Speers on the national bushfire crisis. The broadcast is also being made available to other networks, including on radio. You can tune in from 8:30am.

tweet: While the immediate focus for our emergency services and the Australian Defence Force is keeping people safe and defending against the fires hitting so many areas, we also need to be ready to hit the ground in communities where the fire-front has passed to help them rebuild.

tweet: We're putting an initial $2 billion into a new bushfire recovery fund to ensure the families, farmers and business owners hit by these unprecedented #bushfires get the support they need as they recover.

name: Russell Crowe
tweet:
I love horses. I appreciate and have personal experience of the deep spiritual connection humans and horses can have. I’ve ridden horses for pleasure, for work, I own horses.
These brumbies are wild animals who live without restraint in complete freedom... and I love that too.

name: Russell Crowe
tweet:
The callous destruction of 
4000 of these animals is not the way forward.
Respect need be paid to the intention of the Kosciuszko Wild Horse Heritage Bill and a broader, more detailed plan for now and the future needs to be formulated.

name: Russell Crowe
tweet:
Our literary culture from Banjo Patterson to Eileen Mitchell glorify the Brumby as a symbol of freedom. 
A balance needs to be found here between the environments needs, commercial farming interests and the survival of these noble beasts and the cultural history they represent.

name: Russell Crowe
tweet: and some argue that the presence of horses adjusts the environment, these animals and their lineage have lived in the snowy mountains for close on 200 years. Their forbears traversed this vast continent, connected people, fought in wars and drove Australia’s rural economy

name: Russell Crowe
tweet:
In 2018 there was a piece of legislation called the Kosciuszko Wild Horse Heritage Bill that was supposed to act as protection for the Brumbies. It doesn’t appear to be doing it’s job.

Now while I understand that the horse is an introduced species to the native landscape ...

name: Russell Crowe
tweet: In Australia we call wild horses Brumbies. Americans call them Mustangs. This Thursday in the land and environment court in NSW a decision will be made on the fate of some 4000 beautiful wild horses. If the decision goes against these animals..Track,trap and destroy is the plan.

tweet:
Well Diana, unlike the norm, at a certain point in the mid 90’s my parents moved in with me.

Living in the bush, adjusting things around what’s good for the native flora is a basic responsibility. 

We put bells on her to let birds know she was around .0 casualties .

name: Russell Crowe
tweet:
The point of the story... that kitten, called Cinders ( Cinderella Man ) died yesterday. 
She had never grown to be fully trusting of humans, but, she loved my mum and my mum loved her.

Fairly aggressive with dogs and others, but she never scratched me. I took that as gratitude. pic.twitter.com/WShQH4Sv8P

name: Russell Crowe
tweet:
Angelo asked me, “ I thought you said no cats?”.
I replied that I thought this was the universe telling me to respect my mother and give her what she wanted.
He laughed.
You’re going to be a great boxer he said rather enigmatically “ you believe in destiny “.

name: Russell Crowe
tweet:
There’s something reassuring in a bunch of big sweaty boxers going crazy over a kitten. 
We flew down the hill in a tight group and arrived back at my farm together where I presented my mother with this tiny baby kitten.
She was floored. So happy.

name: Russell Crowe
tweet:
Around 90 mins later at the summit of the punishing hill. The last straggler made the top and we celebrated with cold water and the view of the Orara Valley.
Perfect on this bright hot day, unrolling before us, a fitting reward.
Oh I said... look what I found...

name: Russell Crowe
tweet:
It was so small. Still warm. Mewing and meowing, it’s instinct telling it that it wasn’t in a safe place. 
Black and orange and white.
I picked it up , gave it a pat. 
I looked back down the track and the boys were gaining on me.
I put the kitten in my backpack and rode on.

name: Russell Crowe
tweet:
We were a long way away from any houses.
One thing that came to mind was a car that had passed at the base of the hill.
It’s unusual to see anybody else on these tracks. If you do, invariably they’ll be in a light truck or on a dirt bike. Not a regular car. 
A kitten...abandoned

name: Russell Crowe
tweet:
At one . Zen.

Underneath the swirl of sounds I heard something out of place.
Was that a meow?
I started to look around me .
I heard it again.
I took a few steps of the track into the rain forest. Thick with ferns and vines .
One more step and then I saw it.
A kitten...

name: Russell Crowe
tweet:
I stopped at a good vantage point to look back down the track, have a sip of water , and steel myself for the next section which I knew was the harshest.
Looking back down the track and out through the trees to the valley. Sweat pouring out of me. Bellbirds and cockatoos calling

name: Russell Crowe
tweet: This one particularly punishing hill , around 20km of loose dirt and shale, inexorably rising, definitely sorted the wheat from the chaff. I could look back from higher on the track and see the other lads riding. Some now km’s behind. I was in a zen state, feeling the power ...

name: Russell Crowe
tweet:

All these lads from Canadian and American inner-cities... haha you’re in my territory now...

name: Russell Crowe
tweet:

It was serious business .

My mum kept asking for a cat. In front of all the boxers. I kept saying no.
